============================================================================
COMPLETED 2026-05-19 — Phase F (docs)
============================================================================

DELIVERABLE
-----------
docs/guides/auth-deployment-setup.md (new file, ~330 lines)

Mechanical operator checklist for deploying Spaarke Auth v2 to a fresh
customer tenant. Converts the 2026-05-19 dev cutover steps (recorded in
current-task.md "Operator actions performed" + commit 939e0392) into a
generic, per-env guide with `{placeholder}` substitution markers throughout.

SECTIONS
--------
 1. Prerequisites (resources + tooling that must already exist)
 2. Dataverse environment variables (4 vars — sprk_BffApiBaseUrl,
    sprk_BffApiAppId, sprk_MsalClientId, sprk_TenantId) with set-via paths
    (Maker portal + PAC CLI mention)
 3. App Service configuration (8 settings) with copy-paste az-cli block
    that uses Key Vault references and runs in a single restart cycle
 4. Key Vault secrets inventory (8 named secrets, rotation cadence noted)
 5. Azure AD permissions for MI — three-step recipe:
    5a enumerate BFF app reg's Graph appRoleAssignments
    5b map appRoleId GUIDs to human-readable names
    5c grant each to MI service principal via az rest POST
    5d verify counts match
    (Did NOT hardcode the 11 permission names since the exact list is
    env-dependent; pointed operators at the BFF app reg as canonical source
    and listed the typical 7-8 baseline names. Source data — commit 939e0392
    and the appsettings.template.json _ManagedIdentity_comment only list 4-5
    explicit names; the "11 granted" number from the dev cutover is asserted
    but the discrete list is not in any committed file.)
 6. Dataverse Application User for MI (Power Platform admin center +
    least-privilege role recommendation; multi-env reminder)
 7. Deploy + restart (cross-link to bff-deploy skill)
 8. Verification smoke tests (4 tests — /healthz, OBO endpoint, MI →
    Dataverse via /healthz/dataverse/doc, browser MSAL regression)
    Smoke 8b + 8c are literal copies of the dev-cutover smoke tests that
    passed on 2026-05-19.
 9. Customer responsibilities (CA, MFA, secret rotation cadence, IGA,
    audit log retention, network egress, backup/DR) — per per-tenant model
10. Appendix A — value cheat sheet template (fill-in-the-blank runbook
    sheet for the operator's secrets manager)

SCOPE BOUNDARIES (deferred / outside scope)
-------------------------------------------
- Bicep / IaC templates for the resources themselves — outside scope;
  ENVIRONMENT-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md sections 2-7 cover that ground.
- Exhaustive Graph permission list — operator should enumerate the BFF
  app reg (Step 5a) since the set varies per-module (Email module needs
  Mail.* perms, etc.). Typical 7-8 baseline names listed; total "11"
  count documented as env-specific.
- Discrete CA policy recommendations — customer-owned per per-tenant
  model; we surface that they're customer-owned without prescribing.
- ADR-027 architectural rationale — explicitly out of scope and
  cross-linked as forthcoming (task 090 / Phase F1).

